    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i like the idea of the supernatural feeling like gang activity, that's dark. but i also want to go deeper into the vibe of the people themselves. for the horror to really land, i want the characters to feel like they belong to that \"dangerous\" archetype too—like maybe the residents are just as unpredictable or volatile as the spirits, or even part of the chaos. how can i write the characters so they don't just feel like victims, but instead feel like they're part of that gritty, aggressive environment that makes outsiders so scared of the area?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
