      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To make characters feel intrinsically woven into the chaos, present their aggression not as inherent evil, but as a survival mechanism shaped by the environment. Their paranoia and volatility should be rational responses to a hostile, neglected space, making their actions tragically believable. Develop them as fiercely protective or deeply disillusioned, showing how the constant edge of conflict has hardened them. This positions them as navigators of the darkness, not just sufferers of it.",
      "source": "target",
